Gloriana, Aphro,<br>
<br>
a) I don't care who stole what from who.<br>
b) This post started out in the General category. The only flame I see is that guy who flamed Khael.<br>
c) I didn't actually come here to flame anybody, just relating my observations about things I see in-game.<br>
d) This is a message board, for discussion about stuff. If you don't want to discuss something I bring up, then don't. But to say that I shouldn't bring up a topic because it hits too close to home, or because you find it offensive is pretty uncivilized.<br>
<br>
There's a reason I brought this subject up. Mostly because it had to do with the thread, and also because that sort of exclusion has affect me.<br>
<br>
Have you ever met someone by chance and become friends with them, and then find out that you're 2 levels short of their guild minimum and it's getting raised in a couple days???<br>
<br>
Personality, skill, friendship...none of that meant a damn thing. I guess I just wasn't l33t enough to hang and that was that.<br>
<br>
So when someone says that people left l33t guild #4 to join l33t guild #1, it really doesn't come as a shock when these are the same folks who wouldn't condescend to hang with me because I was level 43 instead of level 45.<br>
<br>
I've also had some good experiences with guilds, and met groups of people for whom attitude was more important than altitude.<br>
<br>
I actually joined a guild on Mith Marr as a level 10 Magician when almost everybody in the guild was in their 40's and 50's. These are people I would do anything for, because they wanted my friendship first and my nukes second.<br>
<br>
Or a guild like LoF on E.Marr, where I was trying to get a FBR in my 20's and Maraxis, without even knowing me, decided to do a good deed for a stranger. He took on Najena, I took on the 2 mages, he bent down, grabbed the robe, gave it to me and said &quot;Enjoy.&quot; When I saw that, I was so impressed I made it my life's mission to join that guild, and no guild could have pulled me away.<br>
<br>
That's all ancient history now, and I would still do anything for anybody in LoF, even though I'm no longer among them (and no, I didn't leave to join another guild.)<br>
<br>
So yeah, if I ever joined a guild where I felt that the guild wanted me for my abilities rather than my friendship, I would have no problem switching to a better guild. If you want me for my friendship, I will never leave your side, but if you show me that's it's all business, then I can be all business too.<br>
<br>
The guild policy sets the tempo. Its members dance to that tune.<br>
<br>
I hope that made sense.<br>
