<br>
I have no idea who you are. I don't know if I've even spoken to you in-game before. But I find your remarks  insulting. Your posts in this thread have managed to malign myself and some of my closest game-friends.<br>
<br>
To think that you can know the length and breadth of my desires and motivations - or anyone with whom you have no association - is extremely arrogant.  <br>
<br>
Over the course of the last 2 years, I have often sent tells to acquaintences and friends expressing interest in having them join my guild. No matter what guildtag I was wearing or they were wearing. There is no malice in this. I play for fun - as does everyone - and I want to play with people whose company I enjoy.  I would wager that every single guilded person who has posted here has done the same. Some of the people who have posted here, insinuating that this is &quot;wrong&quot; have sent me tells of this nature showing an interest in having me join their guild while I was in another guild. It's very hypocritical.<br>
<br>
I would also wager than everyone who has posted in this thread has, at some point, broken associations (intentionaly or not) with in-game companions in order to do something new or associate with new friends in an effort to have more fun. I know specific instances of this occuring involving people who have posted here saying this is a bad thing. I believe it's a mistake to assume there is any malice in it, or that they have done anything &quot;wrong.&quot;<br>
<br>
About the comment made to Shazzi... It's crappy that this comment upset her. But, I really doubt there was any malicious intention on the part of the person who made it. It was just tacky  and resulted in a misunderstanding - it wasn't evil, or really anything that needed to be discussed among hundreds of strangers in a public forum.<br>
<br>
About the &quot;don't recruit from other guilds&quot; unspoken rule in Da`kor. I would ask you, &quot;what is recruiting?&quot; If it's making a friendly jibe and expressing interest in playing with someone that you'd like to get to know or who's ability you respect or an old friend that you haven't seen in a while, how is this wrong? Even if you &quot;need&quot; their class to accomplish an in-game goal, how is this wrong? No one is ever &quot;forced&quot; to change guildtags. Nor is everyone who does so, &quot;[betraying] their friends and [leaving] people behind in the pursuit of loot.&quot; <br>
<br>
And, there is a spirit of competition involved with this game. It's one of the things that makes the game fun. For the most part it's friendly, but it still exists.<br>
<br>
If you have a problem with people leaving your guild for whatever reason, there is really only one solution - don't join a guild. It's the nature of all social organizations to grow, change, evolve, and/or die - in real life and in virtual life.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#575757><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utuan00dorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuan00Dorf</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Veteran</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>381</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#E9D756>3/16/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#E9D756>10:16:26 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: what you say!?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
